headline: Freeport-McMoRan (FCX): Valuation Divergence Shapes Investor Debate as Earnings Growth Lags Market
summary: Freeport-McMoRan (FCX) enters the latest earnings season with numbers that paint a nuanced picture. Revenue growth is forecast at 6.8% per year, trailing the broader US market’s 10% expected pace. Earnings are projected to grow 12.6% annually, once again lagging behind the US average of 15.5%. Net profit margins currently sit at 7.4%, a slight drop from last year’s 7.8%, and the company has reported negative earnings growth this period, making it tough to compare meaningfully to its five-year...

headline: Materials Stocks, Copper Jump After Freeport-McMoRan Earnings. Charts Point to More Upside Ahead.

The  which holds  Freeport-McMoRan  as its fourth-largest position, is up close to 2% since the open. headline: FCX, Alcoa Rise As Copper, Aluminum Prices Heat Up
summary: Freeport-McMoRan cleared third-quarter earnings estimates early Thursday but offered no timeline for restarting production after its Grasberg mine disaster.  FCX stock rose, as the near-term copper contract rose toward the top of its recent trading range.  Meanwhile, Alcoa jumped amid a surge in aluminum prices after posting slightly better-than-forecast results late Wednesday.
